question.en:
Given this code snippet:

class Animal {}
class Dog extends Animal {}
class DogFactory { create() { return new Dog(); } }
class AnimalFactory { create() { return new DogFactory().create(); } }

Why is this NOT a proper Abstract Factory pattern?

