question.en:
Consider this code:

class PaymentProcessor {
  process(strategy) { return strategy.execute(100); }
}
const visa = { execute: (amount) => `Visa: $${amount}` };
const mastercard = { execute: (amount) => `MC: $${amount}` };

Why would replacing this Strategy pattern with State be incorrect?

