question.en:
Consider this code:

class EventEmitter {
  private listeners = new Map();
  on(event, callback) { ... }
  emit(event, data) { ... }
}

class UserComponent {
  constructor(emitter) {
    emitter.on('user-login', this.onLogin);
  }
}

Which pattern does this represent, and what is a key limitation compared to the Observer pattern?

